From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Bluetooth: btbcm: BCM20703A2 chip ID + post-Reset settle + tx-power quirk

Three combined changes to make the Spotify Car Thing's BCM20703A2 BT
controller work with mainline. The intended host attach path is
userspace btattach + bcm protocol; the in-kernel hci_bcm serdev
auto-bind path has independent issues that prevent it from working
on this chip and is out of scope here.

1. Add subver 0x220b -> "BCM20703A2" to bcm_uart_subver_table so the
   firmware lookup picks brcm/BCM20703A2.hcd instead of falling
   through to the generic brcm/BCM.hcd (which doesn't exist in
   linux-firmware for this part).

2. Add a 250 ms msleep after btbcm_reset in btbcm_initialize. The
   chip ACKs the HCI_Reset command-complete event but its internal
   state machine then needs ~200 ms before the UART will answer any
   further command. Without the sleep, Read_Local_Version times out
   (-ETIMEDOUT) and probe fails.

3. Always set HCI_QUIRK_BROKEN_READ_TRANSMIT_POWER from
   btbcm_print_controller_features. This chip's firmware build 0353
   returns a 1-byte (status-only) command-complete for HCI_OP_LE_READ
   _TRANSMIT_POWER (0x204b) instead of the 3-byte BT 5.0 response;
   the generic LE init stage then aborts with -EOPNOTSUPP and
   hci_dev_open fails before bring-up completes. Cost on unaffected
   newer controllers is just less precise tx power reporting.

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Upstream-Status: Pending
---
diff --git a/drivers/bluetooth/btbcm.c b/drivers/bluetooth/btbcm.c
index d33cc70ee..4ffa91cc6 100644
--- a/drivers/bluetooth/btbcm.c
+++ b/drivers/bluetooth/btbcm.c
@@ -469,6 +469,14 @@ static int btbcm_print_controller_features(struct hci_dev *hdev)
 	if (dmi_first_match(disable_broken_read_transmit_power))
 		hci_set_quirk(hdev, HCI_QUIRK_BROKEN_READ_TRANSMIT_POWER);

+	/* BCM20703A2 (Spotify Car Thing) firmware build 0353 returns a
+	 * 1-byte (status-only) command-complete for HCI_OP_LE_READ_TRANSMIT
+	 * _POWER (0x204b) instead of the 3-byte BT 5.0 response. Without
+	 * the quirk the LE init aborts with -EOPNOTSUPP. Set unconditionally:
+	 * cost on unaffected newer controllers is just less precise tx power.
+	 */
+	hci_set_quirk(hdev, HCI_QUIRK_BROKEN_READ_TRANSMIT_POWER);
+
 	return 0;
 }

@@ -515,6 +523,7 @@ static const struct bcm_subver_table bcm_uart_subver_table[] = {
 	{ 0x4106, "BCM4335A0"	},	/* 002.001.006 */
 	{ 0x410c, "BCM43430B0"	},	/* 002.001.012 */
 	{ 0x2119, "BCM4373A0"	},	/* 001.001.025 */
+	{ 0x220b, "BCM20703A2"	},	/* 001.002.011 - Spotify Car Thing */
 	{ }
 };

@@ -585,6 +594,14 @@ int btbcm_initialize(struct hci_dev *hdev, bool *fw_load_done, bool use_autobaud
 	if (err)
 		return err;

+	/* Some Broadcom controllers (BCM20703A2 in the Spotify Car Thing
+	 * confirmed) ACK HCI_Reset's command-complete event but their
+	 * internal state machine then needs ~200 ms before the UART will
+	 * answer any further command. Without this delay, Read_Local_Version
+	 * times out (-ETIMEDOUT) and probe fails.
+	 */
+	msleep(250);
+
 	/* Read Local Version Info */
 	skb = btbcm_read_local_version(hdev);
 	if (IS_ERR(skb))
